Class FeatureElement

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, Data, Element, Identifiable, MapData, Spatial
public class FeatureElement
extends BaseElement

The FeatureElement is a Element class wrapping up a com.esri.mo2.data.feat.Feature object to draw the feature in an element container with a given renderer.

See Also:

getGeometry

public FeatureGeometry getGeometry()
this method returns a reference to the underlying Feature's geometry. Because it is a reference, you can choose to directly modify the geometry of the underlying Feature.

If you choose to make modifications, then you must also use the invalidate method to ensure the geometry changes are noted within the underlying Memory Dataset. If you fail to do so, strange effects may occur when you try to select modified data.

For example you should do something like

BaseFeatureElement element; double dx,dy; element.getGeometry().translate(dx, dy); element.invalidate(); Alternatively, you can use similar methods within this class that modify the Geometry and take care of the invalidate for you. So the equivalent of the above code would be: BaseFeatureElement element; double dx,dy; element.move(dx, dy);

Specified by:
getGeometry in interface MapData
Overrides:
getGeometry in class BaseElement
See Also:
